• Designed an anomaly detection system for motors using vibration and microphone sensors for predictive maintenance. 
• Trained and deployed autoencoder models in PyTorch, reducing inference latency to <50 ms for real-time detection. 
• Implemented multi-threaded data acquisition and pre-processing in C++ on ESP32 (dual-core MCU with Wi-Fi). 
• Automated sensor validation using Python scripts and hardware tests for better performance runs.
